in durchaus vergleichbarer Weise. Die Studien des Bandes, die aus einem Symposion des Sonderforschungsbereichs „Ästhetische Erfahrung im Zeichen der Entgrenzung der Künste“ hervorgegangen sind, untersuchen nach einem Blick auf die an Gewalterfahrungen reiche Geschichte des 5. Jahrhunderts v. Chr. das Spannungsfeld von Gewalt und Ästhetik in den Bereichen von Mythos und Kult, Literatur mit dem Schwerpunkt auf der Tragödie und bildender Kunst.  aIn modern art, central importance is accorded to the diverse experiences of physical and mental violence. The resultant question of the forms of presentation of violence and the reasons for taking pleasure in tragic objects is however one which was already posed in Classical Greece in a comparable fashion. The studies in this volume arose from a symposium run by the Collaborative Research Centers on “Esthetic experience and the dissolution of artistic limits”. After reviewing the history of the 5th century B.C. with its intensive experience of violence, they examine the tension between violence and aesthetics in the fields of myth, cult, and literature with particular reference to tragedy and visual art.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aGreek literature, HellenisticxCongressesxHistory and criticism. 0aGreek literature, HellenisticxHistory and criticismvCongresses. 0aViolence in artvCongresses. 0aViolence in artxCongresses. 0aViolence in literaturevCongresses. 0aViolence in literaturexCongresses. 0aViolence in the theatervCongresses. 0aViolence in the theaterxCongresses. 4aGewaltdarstellung /i.d. Bildenden Kunst. 4aGewaltdarstellung /i.d. Literatur. 4aGriechenland /Altertum. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Greece.2bisacsh  aAntiquity.  aGreece.  aarts.  aliterature.  apottery.1 aBohrer, Karl Heinz, econtributor.4ctb4ht